			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<strong>Company and Position Overview/Requirements:</strong><br />
Merge is one of the Southeast&rsquo;s premier Digital Strategy Agencies, headquartered in Greenville, SC.</p>
<p>
Through our unique Digital Strategy consulting method, we offer clients a comprehensive, strategic methodology to developing results-oriented digital solutions. Merge is looking for a part-time Front End Web Designer that has great design skills/ability, but is also an expert in HTML/CSS.</p>
<p>
<strong>Job Overview</strong>:<br />
Work alongside a team, primarily the Creative Director and Project Manager to provide day to day support for Merge&rsquo;s clients and produce dynamic websites using HTML5, CSS3, JavaScript and other tools. Coordinate with team programmers to prepare websites for back-end development, which will integrate website functionality into open source CMS and Ecommerce systems. Perform routine site updates. Support and assist team members when needed.</p>
<p>
<strong>Job Requirements</strong>:</p>
<ul>
<li>
Capable of converting PSD design into high quality, cross-browser/mobile compatible, valid HTML/CSS markup (PSD to HTML)</li>
<li>
3+ years in hand-coded HTML5, CSS3 and JavaScript</li>
<li>
2+ years of Photoshop and web graphics production experience</li>
<li>
Desire to continually develop skill set and mature within company for professional and financial growth</li>
<li>
Highly organized with excellent time/work management ability</li>
<li>
Minimum of 2-3 years experience in agency environment</li>
<li>
Savvy understanding of UI/UX principles</li>
<li>
Online portofolio demontrasting&nbsp;an excellence in&nbsp;design and code</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Preferred Skills/Experience:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
jQuery Library</li>
<li>
Experience content management systems (WordPress, Drupal and/or Expression Engine a major plus).</li>
<li>
Familiarity with AJAX utilizing JSON/XML.</li>
<li>
Expertise in mobile web UI development</li>
<li>
Understanding of SEO concepts and its implementation</li>
<li>
Version control with Git (or SVN)</li>
<li>
Ability to do light PHP programming</li>
<li>
Familiar with CakePHP a plus</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Part-Time</strong><br />
Currently the position is a temp to perm position. Merge intends to hire the right candidate fulltime, but the timing of such a hire is indefinite (and not guarenteed). Please only apply if you are currently available on a temporary basis.</p>
<p>
<strong>Job Perks:</strong><br />
Leading Digital Solutions Agency, casual work environment, cool NEXT Innovation Center office, happy hours</p>
<p>
<strong>Compensation:</strong><br />
$30 per hour</p>
<p>
This position is for Greenville, SC. Local candidates only please.</p>
